  <div class="right">
    <div id="product-description" class="box">
      <div class="title">Product Description</div>
      <div class="body">
      <div style="padding:10px;border:0px solid;">
        <ul class="redArrows">

          <li>The objective of the Notes is to generate semi-annual coupon payments for investors while offering contingent protection against a slight to moderate decline in the S&P/TSX 60 Index (Price Return Version) over the next five-and-a- half years. The Principal Amount is NOT protected under these Notes.

</li><li> Issuer: Bank of Montreal

</li><li> Medium Term: 5.5-year term to maturity

</li><li> Reference Index: The S&P/TSX 60 Index (Price Return Version) is a large cap index comprising 60 actively traded Canadian companies. The Reference Index is market cap weighted, representing approximately 73% of Canada’s equity market capitalization.*

</li><li> AutoCall Feature: The Notes will be automatically called by the Bank if the Closing Level of the Reference Index is equal to or above the AutoCall Level (i.e., 120% of the Initial Level) on any Observation Date after the third Observation Date. The Notes cannot be automatically called prior to the fourth Observation Date. If the AutoCall feature is triggered, Holders will receive the Principal Amount plus the applicable Coupon on the corresponding Coupon Payment Date (in this case, the “Call Date”). If the Closing Level of the Reference Index is never equal to or above the AutoCall Level on any Observation Date after the third Observation Date, the Notes will not be automatically called by the Bank. If the Notes are automatically called by the Bank before Maturity, the Notes will be cancelled and Holders will not be entitled to receive any subsequent payments in respect of the Notes.

</li><li> Contingent Semi-Annual Coupon Payments: Semi-annual Coupons equal to 6.00% per annum, provided the S&P/TSX 60 Index closes at or above the Coupon Knock-Out Level (i.e. 80% of the Initial Level) on each 6-month Observation Date.

</li><li> Contingent Protection: If the Index Return is negative, the Principal Amount will be fully protected so long as the Final Level is at or above the Barrier Level (i.e. 80% of the Initial Level) on the Final Valuation Date. If the Final Level is below the Barrier Level on the Final Valuation Date, the Maturity Payment will be equal to $100 reduced by the actual Index Return (which will be a negative amount equal to the decline in the Reference Index), subject to the Minimum Payment Amount of $1.00 per Note.

</li><li> Daily secondary market provided by BMO Capital Markets (may be subject to an early trading charge up to 2.50% and other limitations as described in the Prospectus).</li><br/>
      
        </ul>
        </div>
      </div>      
      <div class="arrow"></div>
    </div>   
      


